---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
const gt = (await getCollection('groundtruth')).sort((a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf());
const fmj = (await getCollection('fmj')).sort((a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf());
const latestGt = gt[0];
const latestFmj = fmj[0];
---
<Base>
  <h1>I look for where engineering promises break &mdash; in scale-up, in emissions numbers, in the claims we build systems on.</h1>
  <p class="lead">Two things live here: focused work on measuring climate superpollutants honestly, and a wider notebook on energy, engineering, and whatever else holds my attention.</p>

  <h2 class="kicker">Ground Truth</h2>
  <p>Measuring superpollutants honestly &mdash; whether the tonnes we claim to cut are actually real.</p>
  {latestGt && (
    <p class="muted">Latest: <a href={`/ground-truth/${latestGt.id}/`}>{latestGt.data.title}</a></p>
  )}

  <h2 class="kicker">Finding My Joule</h2>
  <p>A wider notebook &mdash; energy, engineering, process, and tangents. Any register.</p>
  {latestFmj && (
    <p class="muted">Latest: <a href={`/finding-my-joule/${latestFmj.id}/`}>{latestFmj.data.title}</a></p>
  )}
</Base>
